skills/reports/**/quality-scan/**

# OS / editor
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Hybrid-local session guidance (NOT synced with primary — each repo keeps its own)
# See commit message for context; primary repo must mirror this rule + `git rm --cached`
# for the protection to become bidirectional and eliminate delete/modify merge hazards.
next-session-start-here.md

# Slab 7a transient runtime evidence (engagement_decay reports, calibration_tripwire JSONL,
# run_summary.yaml etc. emitted by tests + smoke runs). Per 7a.8 spec line 240:
# "Composition Smoke runs created transient _artifacts/trial-2/engagement_decay_report.md;
# removed it because it was smoke output, not operator-witnessed trial-2 evidence."
# Operator-witnessed trial-2 evidence lives elsewhere (e.g., state/config/runs/<trial-id>/).
_artifacts/

# styleguide-picker advisory lock files (Leg-D R8) - runtime artifacts adjacent to stores, never tracked
*.yaml.lock
*.jsonl.lock

# Course-source media (corpus stays on disk per corpus convention; 5.3GB of
# lecture MP4s under Meeting Recording Trim Deconstructed must never enter git)
course-content/**/*.mp4
course-content/**/*.mov
course-content/**/*.m4a
